# Book Bible — OpenAI Chief Author Mode

**Book:** *Modern Data Systems for Analytics and AI* (v2 rewrite)  
**Constitution:** `books/database-analytics-ai/00_BOOK_BIBLE/`

When writing or revising this book, **use OpenAI via the author pipeline** — do not hand-write prose in chat unless fixing a specific issue.

---

## How to write content

```bash
# Write one section (reads Book Bible + repo, writes to chapters/)
npm run author:write -- --chapter 01-why-data-still-matters --section opening-story

# With extra instructions
npm run author:write -- --chapter 01-why-data-still-matters --section 2 --instructions "Use Meridian Retail Group"

# Overwrite existing section
npm run author:write -- --chapter 01-why-data-still-matters --section opening-story --force

# Full chapter (all sections)
npm run author:chapter -- --book database-analytics-ai --chapter 01-why-data-still-matters --catalog v2 --out chapter
```

**Requires:** `OPENAI_API_KEY` in `.env`

---

## What OpenAI reads (consistency)

| Layer | Source |
|-------|--------|
| System prompt | All 4 Book Bible files (`SYSTEM_PROMPT`, `PROJECT_STATUS`, `AUTHOR_DECISIONS`, `CURRENT_CONTEXT`) |
| Repo context | Prior sections in chapter (full text), all chapter summaries, learning objects, section outline |
| Section rules | `section-catalog-v2.yaml` |

After each write, `PROJECT_STATUS.md` and `CURRENT_CONTEXT.md` are updated automatically.

---

## Cursor agent workflow

1. Read Book Bible files (if not using `npm run author:write` which loads them automatically)
2. Run `npm run author:write` for the target section
3. Review output in `books/database-analytics-ai/chapters/.../sections/`
4. Fix validation issues if any; re-run with `--force` if regenerating
5. Update `PROJECT_STATUS.md` manually if batch-writing multiple sections
6. Commit to Git when a batch is ready (user requests commit explicitly)

---

## Authoring rules (summary)

- WHY → WHAT → WHEN → HOW — never reverse
- 20-section v2 structure (`section-catalog-v2.yaml`)
- Meridian Retail Group for continuity; named companies for industry insight
- ISBX format: YAML frontmatter + Markdown + fenced blocks
- Production mode: full prose, not outlines

---

## Publishing vs authoring

| Mode | When |
|------|------|
| **Authoring** (this rule) | `npm run author*` — OpenAI writes to `books/` |
| **Publishing** | `npm run atlas:publish` — import/deploy only, never rewrite |

See AD-016 in `AUTHOR_DECISIONS.md`.
